methods.name: getActiveColoring

returnValue.description: Value of property activeColoring

methods.description:
Gets current value of property {@link #getActiveColoring activeColoring}. Active coloring configurations. specifies which coloring of the possible colorings is to be applied for the current chart layout. It holds an object with two properties：
  1. coloring: mandatory, specify which kind of coloring should take effect in current chart layout. Possible values refer to {@link sap.chart.ColoringType}
  2. parameters:
    • Criticality supports two parameters: "dimension" and "measure". Both are optional, one (and only one) must be provided. This setting disambiguates when multiple colorings for different visible dimensions and measures are applicable. "measure" supports two input types:
      1. string for single measure name
      2. string[] of multiple measure names(only supported in static), which is relevant in case of a static measure criticality defined on multiple measures.
      "dimension" holds the dimension name as string value.
    • Emphasis supports only one parameter: "dimension" which is optional. "dimension" holds the dimension name as string value.
Example: 
activeColoring: {
    coloring: sap.chart.ColoringType.Criticality,
    parameters: {
        dimension: "AvailabilityStatus”
    }
}

methods.description:
Sets a new value for property {@link #getActiveColoring activeColoring}. Active coloring configurations. specifies which coloring of the possible colorings is to be applied for the current chart layout. It holds an object with two properties：
  1. coloring: mandatory, specify which kind of coloring should take effect in current chart layout. Possible values refer to {@link sap.chart.ColoringType}
  2. parameters:
    • Criticality supports two parameters: "dimension" and "measure". Both are optional, one (and only one) must be provided. This setting disambiguates when multiple colorings for different visible dimensions and measures are applicable. "measure" supports two input types:
      1. string for single measure name
      2. string[] of multiple measure names(only supported in static), which is relevant in case of a static measure criticality defined on multiple measures.
      "dimension" holds the dimension name as string value.
    • Emphasis supports only one parameter: "dimension" which is optional. "dimension" holds the dimension name as string value.
Example: 
activeColoring: {
    coloring: sap.chart.ColoringType.Criticality,
    parameters: {
        dimension: "AvailabilityStatus”
    }
}
When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.

symbols.name: sap.chart.data.Measure
symbols.description:
Definition of a single measure in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut The measure is assigned to feed uid “size”.
scatter The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “valueAxis2”.
bubble The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”.
The first measure with role “axis2”, or (if not exists) the second measure with role “axis1” or (if not exist) the first measure with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis2”.
The remaining measure is assigned to feed uid “bubbleWidth”.
heatmap The measure is assigned to the feed uid “color”.
treemap The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “color”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “weight”.
..dual.. At least one measure is assigned to each of the feed uids “valueAxis” and “valueAxis2”, according to the general rule.

properties.name: axis1
properties.description:
General Rules for all chart types
  1. All measues with role "axis1" are assigned to feed uid "valueaxis". All measures with role "axis2" are assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2". All measures with role "axis3" are assigned to feed uid "bubbleWidth".
  2. If a chart type does not use the feed uid "valueaxis2", then all measures with role "axis2" are treated as measures with role "axis1".
  3. If a chart type requires at least 1 measure on the feed uid "valueaxis" (true for all non-"dual" chart types), but there is no measure with role "axis1", then the first measure with role "axis2" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis"
  4. If the chart type requires at least one measure on the feed uid "valueaxis2" (true for all "dual" chart types"), but there is no measure with role "axis2", then the first measure with role "axis3" or "axis4" or (if not exists) the last measure with role "axis1" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2".

properties.name: axis2
properties.description: Measures with role "axis2" are assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2" if used. If a chart type does not use the feed uid "bubbleWidth" (true for all chart types except bubble and radar), then all measures with role "axis3" or "axis4" are treated as measures with role "axis2".

properties.name: axis3
properties.description: Measures with role "axis3" are assigned to feed uid "bubbleWidth" if used.

properties.name: axis4
properties.description: Once used by Bullet Chart, but as this chart layout is configured via semantic patterns instead, "Asix4" has no special usage from now on.
